bp_xfield_bio: Brian is a Software Development Engineer at BRCK Limited, a company whose focus is building rugged, self-powered mobile Wi-Fi devices. He has worked in the I.T. industry for 6 years, with skills including system administration, software development and I.T. project management. Brian is passionate about serving God and is involved in various ministries such as teaching (pre-teens, teens and young adults) and mentoring young Christian professionals about careers. He has a BSc. in Biotechnology from Kenyatta University and a MSc. in Computer-based Information Systems from Strathmore University.
description: A software developer from Kenya with focus on Front-end web development.  But utmost importance, a follower and servant of Jesus Christ (Romans 1:16)

bp_xfield_bio: I live in Orlando, Florida. I am adigital strategist on the global digital strategies team of Cru. Originally from Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, I spent eight years in Ethiopia, leading 24 countries in Southern and Eastern Africa in digital strategies, before moving to Florida in May 2016. I am passionate about making Jesus known to all cultures and people groups in the world. I and my team help people around the world use digital tools like websites, video, mobile apps and more to help advance the gospel.I work to develop young leaders and empower church leaders to use indigenous digital strategies to reach their own people and culture for Jesus. I have traveled to 33 countries. In my free time, I enjoy walking, watching movies, and watching soccer (especially when my favorite team, Chelsea, is playing).
description: I love Jesus and passionate to make Him known everywhere!
